<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Molene> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The Molène site was a coastal cabled observatory deployed offshore Molène Island in the Iroise Sea between 2012 and 2017. Dedicated to long-term and high-resolution monitoring of coastal biodiversity and biomass, it also served as a testing site for in situ qualification of sensors and marine equipment. The observatory cable was permanently damaged in 2017 and the site was subsequently dismantled."@en .
