<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Iberian_Margin> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The Gulf of Cadiz area is highly important for geo-hazards. It was the location of the devastating 1755 earthquake and tsunami that affected Europe. The convergence of the African and Eurasian tectonic plates makes this region seismically and volcanically active. The Iberian Margin is also a key oceanographic region where Atlantic and Mediterranean waters exchange, influencing the Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation (AMOC). It is the northernmost part of the Canary Current Upwelling System (CCUS), characterised by strong upwelling and mesoscale ocean dynamics. These geological and oceanographic conditions support highly diverse benthic ecosystems and play an important role in the distribution of marine mammals and fish species."@en .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#Karin_SIGLOCH> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://schema.org/Person> .
<https://w3id.org/earthsemantics/OSO#BoundingBox> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Αναπαριστά μια ορθογώνια γεωγραφική περιοχή που ορίζεται από βόρεια, νότια, ανατολικά και δυτικά όρια συντεταγμένων. Η έννοια αυτή είναι ευθυγραμμισμένη με το ISO 19115-3 και διαλειτουργική με τις γεωμετρίες GeoSPARQL."@el .
